Wrath of the Titans
5.8
AdvertisementBy ANDY WEBSTERHey, Perseus! You’ve just dispatched Medusa, a horde of Furies and Seems reasonable for this demigod (Previously, he and Hades (Ralph Fiennes) threatened mankind; now, in That’s about all the plot you get (or need) in this action spectacle. What you get in abundance, as before, are its true stars: monsters in digital (and in some theaters 3-D) detail, notably a chimera; three huge Cyclopes; Makhai (minions with two heads and torsos); and Kronos himself, a lumbering Gargantua of living lava, all engaged in furious, fairly bloodless PG-13 conflict.Of course, in a tradition dating to “Wrath of the Titans” is rated PG-13 (Parents strongly cautioned). It has copious but largely harmless conflagration.





Opens on Friday nationwide.
Directed by Jonathan Liebesman
